Are you the only one

20
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,880
in the dorm right now?

21
00:01:46,800 --> 00:01:48,240
Everyone's gone home for the break.

22
00:01:49,160 --> 00:01:50,400
Thanks for walking me back.

23
00:01:51,760 --> 00:01:53,400
I should thank you
for the thoughtful ballet lessons.

24
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,120
Falling for ballet?

25
00:01:57,880 --> 00:01:58,440
A little.

26
00:01:59,360 --> 00:02:00,720
After just a few days?

27
00:02:01,520 --> 00:02:01,960
Yes.

28
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,680
I'm here.

29
00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:13,680
Okay.

30
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:16,000
Well,

31
00:02:17,480 --> 00:02:18,280
see you next time then.

32
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:22,240
I'm off.

33
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:00,720
Who is it?

34
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,680
Wang Shuhan, you forgot your key again?

35
00:03:07,200 --> 00:03:08,280
How did you get upstairs?

36
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,400
I left my ID with the lady downstairs.

37
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,120
Is something wrong?

38
00:03:17,560 --> 00:03:18,880
Your voice sounded a bit off today.

39
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,160
I made you some pear soup.

40
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:24,320
♪If a tsunami roared inside my heart♪

41
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:27,360
♪Who among the passersby
would hear the wind?♪

42
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:28,400
I simmered this for a long time.

43
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:29,440
Drink it while it's warm.

44
00:03:30,920 --> 00:03:31,560
Thanks.

45
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:34,240
Be careful, it's hot.

46
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:37,200
♪I never dared to hope, yet you came by♪

47
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:44,240
♪And listened to my hesitant life♪

48
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,720
♪We are like wandering kites♪

49
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,840
How old were you
when you started dancing?

50
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:51,640
Four.

51
00:03:52,080 --> 00:03:52,680
So young?

52
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,240
Ballet requires starting at a young age.

53
00:03:55,080 --> 00:03:55,840
Then isn't it too late

54
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,680
for someone like me?

55
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,320
Way too late.

56
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:02,680
♪Who waits on and on?
Who dreams over and over?♪

57
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,560
And you still accepted me?

58
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:05,600
If you're brave enough to come,
I'm brave enough to teach you.

59
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:07,960
Starting is easy.

60
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,440
Sticking with it is the hard part.

61
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:10,840
We'll continue next week then.

62
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,480
I won't be here next week.

63
00:04:12,980 --> 00:04:14,360
♪How rare it is in life
to have someone to like?♪

64
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:14,920
Why?

65
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,280
I'm going to Hongyuan County

66
00:04:16,280 --> 00:04:18,160
in Aba Prefecture, Sichuan,
for a charity trip on my dad's behalf.

67
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:19,600
He goes there

68
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,080
every year.

69
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:23,400
But the company's too busy this year.

70
00:04:23,920 --> 00:04:25,280
So I'm going in his place.

71
00:04:26,520 --> 00:04:27,800
I've never been there before.

72
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:30,920
I hear the sunsets there
are more beautiful than anywhere else.

73
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,020
♪How rare it is for favor
to reunite again?♪

74
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:34,120
Alright.

75
00:04:34,120 --> 00:04:35,040
Then we'll

76
00:04:35,760 --> 00:04:36,840
talk more next time we meet.

77
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:38,920
♪How rare it is that it's still you?♪

78
00:04:38,920 --> 00:04:39,480
Drink up.

79
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:46,580
♪The coming and going crowd
still feigns its haste♪

80
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:47,920
Is it good?

81
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:53,580
♪It teaches us how precious devotion is♪

82
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:59,040
♪To give a lifetime for a single name♪

83
00:04:59,040 --> 00:04:59,640
Thanks.

84
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:01,200
No problem.

85
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:01,840
Well,

86
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:03,400
see you tomorrow.

87
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:05,320
♪If it were you, I'd do the same♪

88
00:05:05,320 --> 00:05:05,920
See you next time.

89
00:05:07,240 --> 00:05:07,680
See you next time.

90
00:05:13,480 --> 00:05:13,920
How about

91
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,880
we get hot pot tomorrow?

92
00:05:17,360 --> 00:05:18,080
A farewell dinner for you.

93
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,240
Okay.

94
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,200
I'm off then.

95
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,080
Bye.

96
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,120
Bye.

97
00:05:28,280 --> 00:05:34,600
