still feigns its haste♪

100
00:05:48,800 --> 00:05:54,960
♪It teaches us how precious devotion is♪

101
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:55,800
Be careful on your way back.

102
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:56,760
[Tan Siting]
Good night.

103
00:05:56,760 --> 00:06:00,080
♪To give a lifetime for a single name♪

104
00:06:00,080 --> 00:06:00,840
[Feng Rui]
Get some rest.

105
00:06:01,040 --> 00:06:01,440
Good night.

106
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:08,700
♪If it were you, I'd do the same♪

107
00:06:13,240 --> 00:06:13,840
Dad!

108
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,160
I can't find my math book!

109
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:17,960
It's in the bookcase.

110
00:06:17,960 --> 00:06:19,160
I looked. It's not there.

111
00:06:20,080 --> 00:06:20,880
Check the drawers.

112
00:06:21,200 --> 00:06:22,160
Not there either.

113
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,160
Let me help you look.

114
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:28,880
See?

115
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:30,760
Look, you put it here
after finishing yesterday.

116
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:41,040
Look at this cut!

117
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,480
Where's the medicine?

118
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,080
It's still bleeding.

119
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:43,680
Go.

120
00:06:43,680 --> 00:06:44,720
Go get the first aid kit.

121
00:06:45,400 --> 00:06:45,880
Dad!

122
00:06:46,640 --> 00:06:47,080
Done?

123
00:06:48,080 --> 00:06:48,480
Give it to me.

124
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,360
Where did you put
the band-aids from yesterday?

125
00:06:51,880 --> 00:06:53,560
No idea. I must have lost it
while I was sleeping.

126
00:06:53,680 --> 00:06:54,400
Where's the medicine?

127
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:55,840
All gone, I guess.

128
00:06:57,680 --> 00:06:58,360
Here.

129
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,960
No. Where is the medicine?

130
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:11,000
It's just a surface wound,

131
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:11,800
but try not to do

132
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,040
any strenuous activity at school today,

133
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:13,600
alright?

134
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:16,200
Give it to me.

135
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,160
Ms. Wen,

136
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,960
thank goodness you're here.

137
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:27,160
If you hadn't come,

138
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,760
I'd definitely be late for school today.

139
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:30,600
Learn from your mistakes.

140
00:07:30,720 --> 00:07:32,120
There's nothing wrong
with standing up for others,

141
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:32,840
but...

142
00:07:32,840 --> 00:07:34,320
There is something wrong with it.

143
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:36,760
While the intention is very good,

144
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:37,680
you're not quite old enough

145
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:38,920
to handle it that way.

146
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,400
Next time something like this happens,

147
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,400
protect yourself first, alright?

148
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:43,280
I understand.

149
00:07:44,240 --> 00:07:45,040
I'm full.

150
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:45,560
Okay.

151
00:07:45,640 --> 00:07:46,240
Can you clear this for me?

152
00:07:46,440 --> 00:07:46,840
Hurry up.

153
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,680
I forgot my red scarf.

154
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,680
Be quick.

155
00:07:51,360 --> 00:07:53,600
We shouldn't take this lightly.

156
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:56,200
Le will be fine.

157
00:07:56,920 --> 00:08:00,120
I'm just worried he's only acting fine.

158
00:08:03,320 --> 00:08:04,000
Okay, hurry up.

159
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,280
Put it on. My bag.

160
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:05,560
Got it.

161
00:08:05,880 --> 00:08:06,160
Let's go.

162
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:06,760
I'll carry it for you.

163
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:07,400
Let's go.

164
00:08:08,080 --> 00:08:09,240
Don't be late.

165
00:08:28,240 --> 00:08:29,320
Are you ready?

166
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,120
Ms. Zhuang, I need to use the restroom.

167
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:33,200
Go ahead.

168
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,080
Be quick.

169
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,480
Why did she come out?

170
00:08:40,560 --> 00:08:41,760
Miss, where's the restroom?

171
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:42,880
Over there.

172
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:43,560
Thanks.

173
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:44,240
No problem.

174
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:45,200
What's she doing out here?

175
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,760
Is she too nervous?

176
00:08:49,120 --> 00:08:51,080
With nerves like that,
how will she ever perform on stage?

177
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:14,200
Are you very nervous?

178
00:09:16,480 --> 00:09:17,240
Don't be.

179
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,400
Ms. Guan may be very strict,

180
00:09:19,640 --> 00:09:21,680
but she's quite good to her students.

181
00:09:24,520 --> 00:09:25,240
Tell you what,

182
00:09:25,520 --> 00:09:26,800
when you see Ms. Guan,

183
00:09:26,880 --> 00:09:27,880
bow to her first

184
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,280
to show respect.

185
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:31,880
It'll put her in a better mood.

186
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,600
Then she might not be as hard on you.

187
00:09:34,920 --> 00:09:37,160
I'm afraid I won't be able to
hold it for a minute.

188
00:09:38,080 --> 00:09:38,960
I'll tell you a secret.

189
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:41,840
There's a water stain
on the classroom ceiling

190
00:09:42,080 --> 00:09:43,280
that looks just like a butterfly.

191
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:45,280
Just look for that.

192
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,840
When you're holding the position,

193
00:09:47,160 --> 00:09:47,600
keep looking for it.

194
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:49,400
Once you find it, the time will be up.

195
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:50,280
Good luck.

196
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:51,480
Don't let Ms. Tan down.

197
00:09:54,520 --> 00:09:55,280
First move.

198
00:09:55,560 --> 00:09:56,080
Plié.

199
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:57,200
Start timing.

200
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,960
Let's move to the next move.

201
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:10,800
Demi-plié.

202
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:11,680
Start timing.

203
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:13,920
Okay.

204
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:15,360
Now try it on one leg.

205
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:22,360
Not bad.

206
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,560
Prepare for the next move.

207
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:24,680
Ready.

208
00:10:25,440 --> 00:10:26,080
Start timing.

209
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,320
Final move.

210
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:28,440
Begin.

211
00:11:15,040 --> 00:11:16,080
Okay. Time's up.

212
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:19,400
That was really good.

213
00:11:20,280 --> 00:11:21,120
Quite good.

214
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:21,560
Yes.

215
00:11:22,280 --> 00:11:22,600
Right.

216
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:23,280
Good.

217
00:11:25,040 --> 00:11:25,480
Madam.

218
00:11:28,920 --> 00:11:29,560
Ms. Guan,

219
00:11:29,560 --> 00:11:31,280
did I pass the exam?

220
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:31,680
Wait a moment.

221
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:33,120
Ms. Zhuang,

222
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,160
here are the compiled results.

223
00:11:34,160 --> 00:11:34,840
Please take a look.

224
00:11:38,280 --> 00:11:39,000
Congratulations.

225
00:11:39,160 --> 00:11:39,840
You passed the exam.

226
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,160
But

227
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:44,360
this school

228
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,320
is not the kind of amateur school
you might think.

229
00:11:46,560 --> 00:11:47,880
To reach our standards,

230
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,600
you'll need to keep working hard.

231
00:11:49,640 --> 00:11:50,840
I understand. I will work hard.

232
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:51,800
Thank you, Madam.

233
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:52,400
Thank you.

234
00:11:52,640 --> 00:11:53,120
Alright.

235
00:11:53,400 --> 00:11:54,400
Ms. Qin will take your mom

236
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,920
to complete
the enrollment procedures later.

237
00:11:58,520 --> 00:11:58,880
Ms. Zhuang.

238
00:12:01,040 --> 00:12:01,400
This way.

239
00:12:02,040 --> 00:12:02,400
Ms. Tan,

240
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:02,960
I'll leave now.

241
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:03,400
Thank you.

242
00:12:04,040 --> 00:12:04,720
Don't just stand around here.

243
00:12:04,760 --> 00:12:06,160
Everyone, back to your classrooms now!

244
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:06,880
Congratulations.

245
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:07,360
Keep up the good work.

246
00:12:07,400 --> 00:12:07,880
Everyone, get out of here.

247
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:11,000
I told you you could do it.

248
00:12:12,280 --> 00:12:13,120
Feeling confident?

249
00:12:13,400 --> 00:12:13,840
Yes.

250
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,120
Madam, are you confident?

251
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:15,680
Yes.

252
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,200
She really did well.

253
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:17,650
Yeah.

254
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:19,000
I knew she could pass.

255
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:20,840
Thank you.

256
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,760
Sir, I came

257
00:12:23,800 --> 00:12:25,960
to apologize.

258
00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:26,680
Well...

259
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:28,680
My grandson,

260
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:29,840
Feng Lexuan.

261
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:31,800
He got into a fight yesterday.

262
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:33,320
I heard from him

263
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:36,160
that some students
were bullying other students.

264
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:39,200
I said, "That can't be right."

265
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:41,120
How could

266
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:43,600
there possibly be bullying
in a school like this?

267
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:44,520
I said he was talking nonsense.

268
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:47,360
I even explained it to him.

269
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:50,160
Severe school bullying

270
00:12:50,520 --> 00:12:52,040
can lead to criminal liability.

271
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,680
The school could be held responsible.

272
00:12:56,000 --> 00:12:57,040
We will

273
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,200
investigate this matter thoroughly.

274
00:12:59,560 --> 00:13:01,160
Once the investigation is complete,

275
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,360
I'll give you a response.

276
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,920
But right now,

277
00:13:04,120 --> 00:13:05,000
there's no evidence.

278
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:07,520
So no one can draw conclusions yet.

279
00:13:07,720 --> 00:13:08,400
Right.

280
00:13:08,880 --> 00:13:09,840
I asked him.

281
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,440
I said, "You claim it's bullying."

282
00:13:11,640 --> 00:13:12,600
"Do you have proof?"

283
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:13,960
"Where is the evidence?"

284
00:13:14,520 --> 00:13:16,680
He said it happened in a blind spot.

285
00:13:22,520 --> 00:13:23,720
Your school

286
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:27,600
has areas not covered
by surveillance cameras?

287
00:13:28,240 --> 00:13:30,960
