579
00:26:38,320 --> 00:26:39,520
makes perfect sense.

580
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:47,200
Ms. Hu,

581
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:51,760
if we're talking about facts,

582
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:53,520
I have something to show everyone.

583
00:27:14,640 --> 00:27:15,280
What are you doing?

584
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,040
The truth is now clear.

585
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,760
On behalf of the school,

586
00:27:32,760 --> 00:27:35,280
I apologize to Feng Lexuan,

587
00:27:35,800 --> 00:27:37,440
Duan Xiyan,

588
00:27:37,440 --> 00:27:38,440
and Yang Zihuan.

589
00:27:38,760 --> 00:27:40,080
You did nothing wrong.

590
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:41,240
On the contrary,

591
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:44,040
Feng Lexuan, Duan Xiyan,
you stood up for a student

592
00:27:44,040 --> 00:27:45,360
being bullied.

593
00:27:45,360 --> 00:27:46,640
You were very brave.

594
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:47,800
The principal said

595
00:27:47,960 --> 00:27:49,440
you will receive certificates
of commendation

596
00:27:49,440 --> 00:27:50,560
at the flag-raising ceremony on Monday.

597
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:53,280
And,

598
00:27:53,720 --> 00:27:56,560
Ren Zhexi, Liu Zixin, Fu Yiwei,

599
00:27:56,560 --> 00:27:57,480
you three

600
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,160
bullied others

601
00:27:59,160 --> 00:28:00,360
and told lies.

602
00:28:00,600 --> 00:28:02,160
You will each receive a major demerit.

603
00:28:02,480 --> 00:28:03,440
In addition,

604
00:28:03,440 --> 00:28:05,120
you are placed on probation.

605
00:28:05,680 --> 00:28:06,680
If there's a next time,

606
00:28:06,680 --> 00:28:07,520
you will be expelled!

607
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:08,640
Is that clear?

608
00:28:11,040 --> 00:28:12,240
Alright. Let's begin class.

609
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,160
That was satisfying.

610
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:17,040
Turn your math books
to page twenty-three.

611
00:28:18,760 --> 00:28:19,160
Dad,

612
00:28:19,520 --> 00:28:20,760
let me use this to toast you.

613
00:28:21,120 --> 00:28:23,760
On behalf of my classmates,
I thank you for helping clear our names.

614
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:24,920
You're welcome.

615
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,600
To your courage in standing up

616
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:36,280
for what's right.

617
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:37,920
Thank you, Grandma.

618
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,080
But next time you encounter
such a situation,

619
00:28:41,080 --> 00:28:42,760
you need to learn
to protect yourself first.

620
00:28:42,880 --> 00:28:43,440
Right.

621
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:44,960
Dad,

622
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:46,200
did you sign me up

623
00:28:46,200 --> 00:28:47,120
for the free combat class yet?

624
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,880
Are you serious about this?

625
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:51,280
Maybe we should
think about it some more.

626
00:28:52,080 --> 00:28:52,560
Dad,

627
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:54,800
do you know how my classmates
praised you?

628
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:55,560
How?

629
00:28:56,040 --> 00:28:58,320
"Feng Lexuan, your dad is super cool,

630
00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,240
inside and out."

631
00:29:01,480 --> 00:29:02,040
Alright.

632
00:29:02,040 --> 00:29:04,000
I'll sign you up
for the free combat class.

633
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,800
Do you know
who you should be most thankful to?

634
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:10,200
It's Ms. Wen.

635
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:12,920
She went to plead your case

636
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:14,000
with that child's mother.

637
00:29:14,480 --> 00:29:15,400
Ms. Wen,

638
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,240
you must have had to endure a lot.

639
00:29:17,240 --> 00:29:17,600
No.

640
00:29:17,600 --> 00:29:18,520
Not at all.

641
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,200
It's

642
00:29:20,200 --> 00:29:21,760
thanks to your dad finding the evidence.

643
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,720
Let me propose another toast
to both of you.

644
00:29:24,160 --> 00:29:24,520
Okay.

645
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:25,600
Let's do it together.

646
00:29:30,680 --> 00:29:31,200
Grandma,

647
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,880
is there anyone else I need to toast?

648
00:29:34,080 --> 00:29:35,160
Can we eat now?

649
00:29:37,480 --> 00:29:38,680
Alright. Let's eat.

650
00:29:47,520 --> 00:29:48,040
Today,

651
00:29:48,320 --> 00:29:51,880
[9th Grade Model Airplane Competition]
we grandly hold the preliminary round

652
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:54,260
of the 9th School-Wide
Model Airplane Competition

653
00:29:54,260 --> 00:29:55,920
on the spring campus sports field.

654
00:29:56,720 --> 00:29:59,520
[Waiting Area]
It aims to foster connection,

655
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:01,520
promote our friendship,

656
00:30:02,000 --> 00:30:04,840
and thereby encourage the healthy
and vibrant development

657
00:30:04,840 --> 00:30:06,880
of our model airplane endeavors.

658
00:30:08,280 --> 00:30:09,120
Finally,

659
00:30:09,120 --> 00:30:10,760
we wish all participants

660
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,560
outstanding results.

661
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:17,120
And we wish this competition
a complete success!

662
00:30:17,120 --> 00:30:18,600
[Audience Area]

663
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:22,200
The competition is about to
officially begin!

664
00:30:22,840 --> 00:30:27,400
Come on!

665
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:29,320
Let's have some louder cheers, alright?

666
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:37,400
Go for it!

667
00:30:37,560 --> 00:30:40,240
Contestant number twelve,

668
00:30:40,600 --> 00:30:41,840
Feng Lexuan!

669
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:43,760
Let's hear some cheers for them!

670
00:30:48,360 --> 00:30:49,120
Come on!

671
00:30:55,160 --> 00:31:04,000
Go for it!

672
00:31:07,160 --> 00:31:07,840
I'll surpass you.

673
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:09,720
Contestants, please take a short break.

674
00:31:20,200 --> 00:31:25,240
Go for it!

675
00:31:25,240 --> 00:31:27,160
Now we'll announce the results.

676
00:31:27,320 --> 00:31:28,760
Third place goes to

677
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,800
Xue Xiaofan!

678
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,040
Second place

679
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:35,680
goes to Feng Lexuan's team!

680
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:38,000
Their time is 30.11 seconds!

681
00:31:38,560 --> 00:31:39,320
Now we'll announce...

682
00:31:39,320 --> 00:31:40,000
We came in second.

683
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,360
I wanted first place.

684
00:31:41,360 --> 00:31:42,960
Let's see who got first.

685
00:31:43,400 --> 00:31:45,160
Ren Zhexi's team!

686
00:31:45,160 --> 00:31:45,880
Their time is

687
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,160
29.05 seconds!

688
00:31:47,160 --> 00:31:47,600
Congratulations!

689
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:51,680
Not good enough.

690
00:31:52,840 --> 00:31:54,240
Go home and practice more.

691
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,400
You can ask me if you have

692
00:31:55,480 --> 00:31:55,720
any questions.

693
00:31:55,720 --> 00:31:56,200
Ms. Tan.

694
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,480
Okay. Bye, Madam.

695
00:31:58,160 --> 00:31:58,800
Qu Zhen?

696
00:32:00,080 --> 00:32:01,200
What are you doing sitting here?

697
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:04,880
Ms. Tan, how were my moves just now?

698
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:09,080
You're stretching by yourself here?

699
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,840
Hip opening and leg stretches
are fundamental skills.

700
00:32:13,080 --> 00:32:14,440
You should practice them properly.

701
00:32:15,640 --> 00:32:16,360
But

702
00:32:16,360 --> 00:32:17,280
there's one thing

703
00:32:17,640 --> 00:32:18,880
you need to pay attention to
when stretching.

704
00:32:19,320 --> 00:32:21,600
Your hips must be aligned correctly.

705
00:32:21,800 --> 00:32:23,520
Many people don't notice that.

706
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,360
Before my mom left,

707
00:32:25,360 --> 00:32:27,400
I promised her I would practice hard.

708
00:32:29,840 --> 00:32:30,640
Keep it up.

709
00:32:40,600 --> 00:32:42,080
Should we get her shoes one size larger?

710
00:32:42,480 --> 00:32:43,400
Sure.

711
00:32:44,560 --> 00:32:45,240
Big feet.

712
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:47,480
And this color, please.

713
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:48,720
Get her two more pairs

714
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:50,520
of the genuine leather ones too.

715
00:32:51,040 --> 00:32:52,640
Two pairs, one size larger.

716
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:53,200
Okay.

717
00:32:53,200 --> 00:32:54,040
Welcome to come again.

718
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:54,320
Okay.

719
00:32:54,360 --> 00:32:54,920
Thank you.

720
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:57,200
Thank you, Ms. Tan.

721
00:32:57,200 --> 00:32:58,160
Keep dancing well.

722
00:33:00,120 --> 00:33:01,360
This doesn't make sense.

723
00:33:02,040 --> 00:33:03,440
How could they win?

724
00:33:07,400 --> 00:33:08,800
You're still thinking about that?

725
00:33:09,320 --> 00:33:11,040
Wasn't it just for fun?

726
00:33:11,760 --> 00:33:14,080
Grandma, it's not just for fun.

727
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,440
A model airplane competition
is a science-based competition.

728
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:20,480
And it's not that I'm afraid
of losing or that I'm unhappy.

729
00:33:21,480 --> 00:33:23,000
I just don't understand

730
00:33:23,600 --> 00:33:24,400
why Ren Zhexi's team

731
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:26,320
ended up taking first place.

732
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:28,640
Ren Zhexi and his friends
had never built model aircraft before.

733
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:31,360
They suddenly decided to
enter this competition

734
00:33:31,360 --> 00:33:33,120
and ended up taking first place.

735
00:33:33,560 --> 00:33:34,800
It's just too strange.

736
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:38,680
Hello?

737
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:41,200
Feng Lexuan, major intel.

738
00:33:41,720 --> 00:33:42,680
What intel?

739
00:33:43,160 --> 00:33:45,200
I just heard from Ji Sen in Class 3

740
00:33:45,200 --> 00:33:46,400
that Ren Zhexi's team

741
00:33:46,400 --> 00:33:47,760
didn't even build
their model airplane themselves.

742
00:33:48,040 --> 00:33:49,480
They didn't build it themselves?

743
00:33:50,240 --> 00:33:53,360
Right. They say they bought it.

744
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:54,840
Seems they spent a lot of money on it.

745
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:56,680
What's the conclusion?

746
00:33:57,320 --> 00:33:58,800
Their model airplane

747
00:33:58,800 --> 00:34:01,080
wasn't built by them at all.

748
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,640
They bought it.

749
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:06,040
Are you allowed to buy it?

750
00:34:06,040 --> 00:34:07,760
They bought it secretly.

751
00:34:07,760 --> 00:34:08,960
The teachers didn't know.

752
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:11,040
I knew it.

753
00:34:11,480 --> 00:34:12,480
The three of them?

754
00:34:12,640 --> 00:34:14,160
Pigs might fly.

755
00:34:14,360 --> 00:34:15,440
How could they?

756
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,640
You don't need to wear
your old shoes anymore.

757
00:34:22,040 --> 00:34:23,680
From now on, you can practice
in these new ones.

758
00:34:24,080 --> 00:34:25,040
Great.

759
00:34:31,440 --> 00:34:33,040
The weather is nice today, isn't it?

760
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:35,440
Ms. Zhuang.

761
00:34:36,160 --> 00:34:37,000
Ms. Zhuang.

762
00:34:38,040 --> 00:34:39,400
Qu Zhen, you went to buy shoes?

763
00:34:39,640 --> 00:34:40,200
Yes.

764
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:43,320
Look, Ms. Tan picked them for me.

765
00:34:43,720 --> 00:34:45,760
She said they're
special soft-soled shoes for dancing.

766
00:34:47,400 --> 00:34:48,200
What brings you here?

767
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:50,560
Mr. Wang said he's your friend.

768
00:34:50,560 --> 00:34:52,120
He sponsored our school today.

769
00:34:52,400 --> 00:34:53,520
I told Ms. Zhuang

770
00:34:53,640 --> 00:34:54,240
it was because of you

771
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:56,040
that I learned
about this wonderful school.

772
00:34:56,600 --> 00:34:59,200
Actually, I've always admired ballet,

773
00:34:59,640 --> 00:35:01,120
and I've always hoped
to do something for it.

774
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:02,440
So thank you, Ms. Zhuang,

775
00:35:02,640 --> 00:35:03,400
for giving me this opportunity.

776
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:05,480
On behalf of our students,

777
00:35:05,680 --> 00:35:07,280
I thank you for your generosity.

778
00:35:07,560 --> 00:35:08,440
You're too kind.

779
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,600
So you're Qu Zhen?

780
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:12,360
Yes.

781
00:35:12,360 --> 00:35:13,200
I heard from Ms. Zhuang

782
00:35:13,200 --> 00:35:15,680
that you're the first Tibetan girl

783
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:16,960
at the school to learn ballet.

784
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:18,680
Nice to meet you.

785
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:20,520
Nice to meet you too.

786
00:35:21,720 --> 00:35:22,160
Ms. Zhuang,

787
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,240
may I invite Ms. Tan and Qu Zhen

788
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:25,120
for a meal?

789
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,320
I should be the one inviting you.

790
00:35:27,760 --> 00:35:29,480
You've made
such a big contribution to our school.

791
00:35:29,640 --> 00:35:30,280
Right?

792
00:35:32,080 --> 00:35:32,680
Ms. Zhuang,

793
00:35:32,920 --> 00:35:33,600
please join us.

794
00:35:33,960 --> 00:35:34,760
I won't go.

795
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:35,480
You go ahead.

796
00:35:35,760 --> 00:35:38,000
I have several students to meet.

797
00:35:38,640 --> 00:35:39,560
Do you need my help?

798
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:40,320
No need.

799
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:41,440
There are plenty of other teachers.

800
00:35:41,880 --> 00:35:42,640
Besides,

801
00:35:42,640 --> 00:35:44,360
properly thanking Mr. Wang on my behalf

802
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,560
is the most important thing.

803
00:35:46,240 --> 00:35:46,840
Alright.

804
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:47,680
Go ahead.

805
00:35:47,880 --> 00:35:50,440
Celebrate for Qu Zhen.

806
00:35:53,160 --> 00:35:53,840
What should we eat?

807
00:35:55,160 --> 00:35:56,440
Let's have pizza.

808
00:35:56,560 --> 00:35:57,560
Is that place still open?

809
00:35:58,840 --> 00:36:00,920
I've only seen pizza in magazines.

810
00:36:00,920 --> 00:36:02,120
I've never tried it.

811
00:36:02,600 --> 00:36:03,640
What does it taste like?

812
00:36:03,880 --> 00:36:04,800
You'll know once you try it.

813
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:05,480
Let's go.

814
00:36:07,240 --> 00:36:08,400
Yes, those two in the front.

815
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:09,240
Add one more of that thing in front.

816
00:36:09,240 --> 00:36:09,880
Are you sure?

817
00:36:10,880 --> 00:36:11,560
That...

818
00:36:12,320 --> 00:36:13,160
Kids!

819
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,120
Take it.

820
00:36:14,120 --> 00:36:14,560
Grandma.

821
00:36:15,120 --> 00:36:15,560
Here.

822
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,080
Well?

823
00:36:19,960 --> 00:36:20,840
What do you think?

824
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:22,720
Look at the quality, Yang Zihuan.

825
00:36:23,400 --> 00:36:23,640
Look.

826
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,520
It's not even on our level.

827
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:27,080
Can we beat them?

828
00:36:27,080 --> 00:36:28,320
Seems like it's imported.

829
00:36:29,160 --> 00:36:30,160
Let me see!

830
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:31,600
Hurry!

831
00:36:31,600 --> 00:36:32,280
Look.

832
00:36:36,160 --> 00:36:36,560
Grandma,

833
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:37,960
where did you get this?

834
00:36:40,400 --> 00:36:42,280
I had it specially made for you.

835
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:43,600
Will

836
00:36:43,880 --> 00:36:44,800
this work?

837
00:36:45,400 --> 00:36:46,960
I had a designer

838
00:36:46,960 --> 00:36:49,160
from the Aerospace Academy
make this for you.

839
00:36:49,440 --> 00:36:51,120
Beating them won't be a problem at all.

840
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:53,760
No.

841
00:36:55,080 --> 00:36:55,840
The competition

842
00:36:55,840 --> 00:36:57,640
is about building
the model airplanes ourselves.

843
00:36:57,960 --> 00:36:58,520
Is it?

844
00:36:58,560 --> 00:36:59,080
But you're just

845
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:00,800
giving us such a high-end one.

846
00:37:00,840 --> 00:37:03,040
It's obvious the three of us
didn't make it ourselves.

847
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:04,480
Yeah.

848
00:37:04,800 --> 00:37:06,800
That's a bit like cheating.

849
00:37:07,160 --> 00:37:08,560
But it's already bought.

850
00:37:09,240 --> 00:37:11,560
Wouldn't it be a waste not to use it?

851
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,320
They bought theirs,

852
00:37:16,640 --> 00:37:17,840
but we have to make ours.

853
00:37:18,520 --> 00:37:19,800
How is that fair?

854
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,760
They bought theirs,
so we should buy one too.

855
00:37:22,920 --> 00:37:24,200
And we have to beat them!

856
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:26,000
Teach those rotten kids a lesson.

857
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:26,720
Right?

858
00:37:27,160 --> 00:37:27,880
But...

859
00:37:27,960 --> 00:37:29,200
That makes sense.

860
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:30,240
Right?

861
00:37:30,400 --> 00:37:31,600
Madam, you're amazing.

862
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:32,760
This time,

863
00:37:33,120 --> 00:37:34,920
we'll really teach Ren Zhexi a lesson.

864
00:37:34,920 --> 00:37:35,360
Look.

